## Key Parsing Rules

1. **Exact Values Only** - Extract precise pixel values, never approximate
2. **Complete Inventory** - List every unique component and token value found
3. **No Assumptions** - If a component pattern is unclear, ask for clarification
4. **Reference Other Rules** - Use ReadRule() to access component and token documentation, don't duplicate their content

## Common Figma Component Patterns

| Figma Pattern | IDS Package |
|--------------|--------------|
| `01 - Button` | @ids-ts/button |
| `01 - Large Card`, `01 - Expandable Card` | @ids-ts/card |
| `02 - Text Status Badge`, `01 - Icon Status Badge` | @ids-ts/badge |
| `02 - Search Input` | @ids-ts/input |
| `.Typography`, headings, body text | @ids-ts/typography |
| Named icons (search, notification, cart, etc.) | Custom Icon component |
| `01 - Control` | Button or icon button |

## Implementation Guidelines

After extraction and analysis, proceed to implementation using the identified components and tokens. Refer to individual component rules and token rules for specific usage guidelines.

## Common Mistakes

You are NOT following this rule properly if you:

- Implement Figma designs without reading this rule first
- Skip the analysis and go straight to code
- Don't extract and list all IDS components detected
- Don't read individual component rules for identified components
- Use hardcoded values instead of design tokens
- Create custom components when IDS equivalents exist
- Ignore the Figma component naming patterns
- Convert designs without verifying proper IDS component mapping